Interface UnitController


  • public interface UnitController
    Each unit has associated an instance of this class. It allows the unit to interact with the environment.

      • canMoveBall

        boolean canMoveBall(Direction dir)
        Returns if the unit can grab/put a ball at the target Direction. It returns true if and only if this unit is a pitcher and either (a) it doesn't have a ball currently in its possession but there is a ball following the given direction, or (b) if it has a ball and the location following the given direction is empty, inside the map, and does not have water. It receives a penalty if the given direction is null. It costs 20 energy.
        Parameters:
        dir - Target direction
        Returns:
        if the unit can grab/put a ball at the target Direction.

      • moveBall

        void moveBall(Direction dir)
        The unit attempts to grab/put a ball at the target Direction. If the unit is a pitcher with already a ball in its possession, it tries to put it. Otherwise, it tries to grab it. This unit receives a penalty if it can't perform the action. It costs 20 energy.
        Parameters:
        dir - Given direction.

      • canBat

        boolean canBat(Direction dir,
               int strength)
        Returns if this unit can bat whatever is located at the given direction. Returns true if and only if this unit is a Batter, there is a ball, a pitcher, a batter or a catcher following the given direction. and the strength is between 1 and the maximum strength. It receives a penalty if the given direction is null. It costs 20 energy.
        Parameters:
        dir - given direction.
        strength - given strength.
        Returns:
        if this unit can bat whatever is located at the given direction.

      • bat

        void bat(Direction dir,
         int strength)
        The unit attemts to bat whatever is located at the given direction. This unit receives a penalty if it can't perform the action. It costs 20 energy.
        Parameters:
        dir - given direction
        strength - given strength

      • canSenseLocation

        boolean canSenseLocation(Location loc)
        Returns if the unit can sense target location. It returns true if and only if the location is on the map, inside the unit's vision range, and if it has enough illumination. It receives a penalty if the given location is null. It costs 10 energy.
        Parameters:
        loc - Target location.
        Returns:
        if the unit can sense target location.

      • isOutOfMap

        boolean isOutOfMap(Location loc)
        Returns if the given location is outside the map. It returns true if and only if the location is inside the unit's vision radius and outside of the map. It receives a penalty if the given location is null or outside of the unit's vision radius. It costs 10 energy.
        Parameters:
        loc - Given location
        Returns:
        if the given location is outside the map.

      • senseObjects

        Location[] senseObjects(MapObject mapObject,
                        float radiusSquared)
        Returns an array with all visible objects inside the map and inside a given radius. It receives a penalty if the given radius is negative or if the object is null. It costs 200 energy.
        Parameters:
        mapObject - Given object
        radiusSquared - Given radius (squared)
        Returns:
        an array with all visible objects inside the map and inside a given radius.

      • senseUnitAtLocation

        UnitInfo senseUnitAtLocation(Location loc)
        Returns the information of the unit at a given location. It returns null if there is no unit. It receives a penalty if the given location cannot be sensed by this unit. It costs 10 energy.
        Parameters:
        loc - Given location
        Returns:
        the information of the unit at a given location.

      • senseUnits

        UnitInfo[] senseUnits(float radiusSquared,
                      Team team)
        Returns an array with all other units of a given team that can be sensed by this unit inside of a given radius around it. It receives a penalty if the radius is negative. If the team is null, it returns the units of all teams. It costs 200 energy.
        Parameters:
        radiusSquared - Given radius (squared)
        team - Given team
        Returns:
        an array with all other units of a given team that can be sensed by this unit inside of a given radius around it.

      • senseObjectAtLocation

                                boolean checkBall)
        Returns the information of the object at a given location. It receives a penalty if the given location cannot be sensed by this unit. It costs 10 energy.
        Parameters:
        loc - Given location
        checkBall - If true, whenever there is a ball it returns "BALL" instead of the object below.
